about.description:
Telemetry provides a configurable traitlets object, EventLog,
for structured event-logging in Python.
It leverages Python’s standard logging library for filtering, handling, and recording events.
All events are validated (using jsonschema) against registered JSON schemas.
about.summary: Telemetry for Jupyter Applications and extensions.

name: jupyter_telemetry
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyter_telemetry" %}
{% set version = "0.0.5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d3eaac14be17510a4d288f3737580107ce14eef543e6133d56654d3f0e742b9b

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    - jsonschema
    - traitlets
    - ruamel.yaml
    - python-json-logger

test:
  imports:
    - jupyter_telemetry

about:
  home: https://jupyter-telemetry.readthedocs.io
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Telemetry for Jupyter Applications and extensions.'

  description: |
    Telemetry provides a configurable traitlets object, EventLog,
    for structured event-logging in Python.
    It leverages Python’s standard logging library for filtering, handling, and recording events.
    All events are validated (using jsonschema) against registered JSON schemas.
  doc_url: https://jupyter-telemetry.readthedocs.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/jupyter/telemetry

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - minrk
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.16
